The paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Wikipedia articles as input, which suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
